FBIS4-5017 "dreas067__a94018" FBIS-EAS-94-067-A Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 ANNEX North Korea Chongnyon Source: Kim Chong-il Given Full Power Chongnyon Source: Kim Chong-il Given Full Power OW0704093394 Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Apr 94 Evening Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0704093394 Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Ho Chong-man, responsible vice chairman of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan [Chongnyon], said he believes "DPRK (North Korean) President Kim Il-song has delegated full power -- political, economic, and military -- to Workers' Party of Korea Secretary Kim Chong-il." He made the remark in an address at a meeting of the Social Democratic Party of Japan's Japan-Korea Committee held at the First Dietmen's Hall on the morning of 5 April. Vice Chairman Ho said he had talks with Secretary Kim Chong-il for about two hours when he visited North Korea from 15 February to 1 March. Ho denied rumors that Kim had been seriously injured, saying "he was in excellent health."
